summary: It was bound to happen sooner or later, but a winter storm has cancelled school and postponed our first Fun Fact of the year......
caption:
It was bound to happen sooner or later, but a winter storm has cancelled school and postponed our first Fun Fact of the year… So keep warm, stay inside today, and enjoy this short episode from the 1960s Spider-Man animated series titled “Trouble with Snow!” ❄️

A snowman is brought to life after being struck by an electrical cable and starts wreaking havoc on the city. Why the cable didn’t melt him is anyone’s guess, but apparently the reason he’s alive is because there are chemicals in the snow… Solves everything. ⛄

summary: Anyone who minimizes Peter and Betty’s old relationship, be it by saying Gwen was his first love, by having Peter say he only...
body: Anyone who minimizes Peter and Betty’s old relationship, be it by saying Gwen was his first love, by having Peter say he only had a crush on her because she was the first person who was nice to him outside of his aunt and uncle, or by having Betty dismiss their relationship as “a long time ago”, say he wasn’t there when his brother died (when he had actually tracked her down when she left the city to help her with it) and talk about the time he went out as Spider-Man when he had a debilitating illness as “he had a cruch on me and I was fond of him” has a micro dick energy.

Okay but every time something small happens, like his webbing shooting everywhere or when he knocks his toe against the edge of a table (oof), he just stares into the distance and says is a serious tone: “several bad choices have led me to this moment” or “I now know why Jesus died. To get away from our shit”

BUT when something major happens, like him getting shot or getting attacked by monsters in all directions, Peter just. He just contently alerts someone of his situation or starts thinking about unnecessary things like: “oh hey mr stark wHHHaaaAtsss poppin? summary: Here's something neat: Just before the North American Video Game Crash of 1983, Marvel Comics briefly produced a single volume...
body: Here’s something neat: Just before the North American Video Game Crash of 1983, Marvel Comics briefly produced a single volume of gaming magazines. The magazine, Blip, covered everything from celebrity and game designer interviews, monthly high score contests/leader boards, gaming strategies, and game previews. The magazine didn’t sell well for many reasons, mostly attributed to the game crash, but the first two issues had a Donkey Kong mini comic and a preview of Spider-Man The Video Game (Atari 2600) with an interview with Stan Lee.

summary: If we do get Peter Parker in the Venom Verse
body:
If we do get Peter Parker in the Venom Verse

Just saying I feel Freddie Highmore would be a excellent choice as a older Spider-Man if Sony decides to do that. Or whatever choice you want. Was listening to the Venom rap by Eninem twice and remembered that casting I like. Yet it’s your choice whoever else maybe Dylan O'Brien or not Peter Parker. I’m just not interested in the MCU Spider-Man meeting Venom.

I’d rather have a adult Spider-Man already experienced enough. Whether that’s The Amazing Spider-Man movie version some how or a new version in this new Venom verse with the new movie.

Just giving my honest thoughts I’m all for hearing opinions whether you want Peter or not. Edit decided to put the Freddie and Dylan tag because I mentioned them.
